books.description: This volume discusses the rich and interesting properties of dynamical systems that appear in ecology and environmental sciences. It provides a fascinating survey of the theory of dynamical systems in ecology and environmental science. Each chapter introduces students and scholars to the state-of-the-art in an exciting area, presents new results, and inspires future contributions to mathematical modeling in ecology and environmental sciences.
books.title: Mathematics for Ecology and Environmental Sciences
books.authors: Yasuhiro Takeuchi, Yoh Iwasa, Kazunori Sato
